14:49.716 --> 14:51.994
[speaking Swahili]

14:52.029 --> 14:54.134
Art is the reflection of
the community.

14:54.169 --> 14:58.656
♪

14:58.690 --> 15:01.935
- Well, what we did is
to make art--

15:01.970 --> 15:03.454
we use it as
a tool.

15:03.488 --> 15:06.043
♪

15:06.077 --> 15:08.286
- So many stories
have been told about Kibera.

15:08.321 --> 15:10.081
- They're negative stories.
- Negative stories.

15:10.116 --> 15:11.565
- Right.
- Many organizations come here

15:11.600 --> 15:15.017
in Kibera, they shoot videos
and films

15:15.052 --> 15:18.641
talking about AIDS, drugs,
you know,

15:18.676 --> 15:20.471
negative things
about Kibera.

15:20.505 --> 15:22.231
- So you have a lot of
documentary crews

15:22.266 --> 15:24.682
that come through here and film
crews that come through here?

15:24.716 --> 15:26.201
- They usually
come here.

15:26.235 --> 15:28.513
- So my question--I have
a question. Are we assholes?

15:28.548 --> 15:30.584
[laughter]

15:30.619 --> 15:32.207
- I was waiting for that.
I feel like an asshole.

15:32.241 --> 15:34.002
- We can talk around it.
We can talk--

15:34.036 --> 15:35.141
I feel like a white guy
right now,

15:35.175 --> 15:36.349
you know
what I mean?

15:36.383 --> 15:38.661
[upbeat music]

15:38.696 --> 15:41.181
- Kibera is massive.

15:41.216 --> 15:45.082
