live here.

15:45.116 --> 15:46.635
♪

15:46.669 --> 15:48.292
A sprawling warren
of homes,

15:48.326 --> 15:51.157
places of worship,
and small businesses

15:51.191 --> 15:53.504
competing for
an edge.

15:53.538 --> 15:57.163
It houses a great part of
Nairobi's labor force.

15:57.197 --> 16:01.477
Meaning no Kibera,
the city grinds to a halt.

16:01.512 --> 16:03.583
- So here,
as a person named Kamau,

16:03.617 --> 16:04.998
I'm not unique.
- Yeah, yeah.

16:05.033 --> 16:07.518
- Yeah.
You're very common.

16:07.552 --> 16:09.209
- You're common.
- It's a common name here.

16:09.244 --> 16:11.384
- I've waited all my life
to be common.

16:11.418 --> 16:15.319
- Welcome home. I'll go and tell
our forefathers you are here.

16:15.353 --> 16:17.183
- Thank you,
thank you.

16:17.217 --> 16:19.564
- Mammito Eunice is
a comedienne,

16:19.599 --> 16:22.050
Simon Okuku,
a musician,

16:22.084 --> 16:25.329
and Jeff Ochieng, once voted
Kenya's funniest person,

16:25.363 --> 16:27.745
are all using art to
tell a new story

16:27.779 --> 16:29.712
about Kibera.

16:29.747 --> 16:32.508
- It started from the challenge
that we had been facing

16:32.543 --> 16:34.648
in this life,
like me.

16:34.683 --> 16:37.168
You know, me, I've been
brought up by a single parent.

16:37.203 --> 16:39.481
I used even to engage in
criminal activities.

16:39.515 --> 16:40.654
- Mm-hmm.

16:40.689 --> 16:43.174
- Coming across
my fellow friends

16:43.209 --> 16:44.486
and who have been passing to
church candle

16:44.520 --> 16:48.041
for masses,
we decided to come up with

16:48.076 --> 16:51.596
our organization known as
Kibera Creative Arts.

16:51.631 --> 16:55.186
So to try to teach this
our fellow young people

16:55.221 --> 16:58.776
to make them avoid getting
into these traps

16:58.810 --> 17:00.191
that are set for us.

17:00.226 --> 17:02.573
[upbeat music]

17:02.607 --> 17:04.713
- Kibera is also
ground zero

17:04.747 --> 17:08.130
for what's called around here
the white savior complex,

17:08.165 --> 17:11.133
a focal point for
the more than 12,000

17:11.168 --> 17:13.239
mostly well-meaning
expat aid workers

17:13.273 --> 17:16.173
who live in Kenya.

17:16.207 --> 17:18.761
It's a dynamic that can be
counterproductive.

17:18.796 --> 17:20.694
The salary and employment
discrepancies

17:20.729 --> 17:23.145
can cause a ripple effect
of problems

17:23.180 --> 17:24.664
for native Kenyans.

17:24.698 --> 17:26.424
- [speaking native language]

17:26.459 --> 17:28.150
- Yeah, man.

17:28.185 --> 17:30.359
- Many Kenyans are working on
a grassroots level

17:30.394 --> 17:32.879
to take control of
their own future.

17:32.913 --> 17:35.847
Kibera Creative Arts
being an example.

17:35.882 --> 17:38.195
Artists and performers from
the neighborhood

17:38.229 --> 17:41.681
working to support and develop
local talent.

17:41.715 --> 17:43.717
- What is it like to be
a comedian in Kenya?

17:43.752 --> 17:45.443
How does that--
how does that look?

17:45.478 --> 17:48.343
- It's so hard to make people
laugh in Kenya.

17:48.377 --> 17:52.830
Imagine these are people who
have not paid their rent.

17:52.864 --> 17:55.764
These are people who have
gone without food

17:55.798 --> 17:57.179
for some days.
- Yeah.

17:57.214 --> 17:58.698
- So they come in angry.
- Yeah.

17:58.732 --> 18:00.838
- Angry and hungry.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

18:00.872 --> 18:04.393
- You should take me with this
camera out when I was small.

18:04.428 --> 18:08.397
Now that I'm grown big,
let me be taken by this camera.

18:08.432 --> 18:12.850
- Another reason why we go
onstage and make people laugh

18:12.884 --> 18:15.887
it is a flash that we would
say, "Wow, man!"

18:15.922 --> 18:19.581
[upbeat music]

18:19.615 --> 18:22.860
♪

18:22.894 --> 18:24.896
- I love to make
more people happy

18:24.931 --> 18:27.727
because there's always
ups and downs in life

18:27.761 --> 18:31.248
but we will
always laugh.

18:31.282 --> 18:33.250
- You know, when people see
Mammito performing

18:33.284 --> 18:36.184
and they see all the people
seeing Mammito as a star.

18:36.218 --> 18:38.255
If Mammito is
just performing

18:38.289 --> 18:41.154
and she's now a star, I don't
need to go and rob somewhere

18:41.189 --> 18:42.776
to make me a star.

18:42.811 --> 18:45.848
I can use whatever I am
because I think even in Kibera

18:45.883 --> 18:47.954
we have something that
we can show to the world.

18:47.988 --> 18:49.507
- [speaking native language]

18:49.542 --> 18:56.756
♪

19:00.587 --> 19:01.968
[upbeat music]

19:02.002 --> 19:03.866
