Beautiful.

27:05.347 --> 27:06.694
- Not a problem.

27:06.728 --> 27:10.352
- Man, honestly,
this looks really good.

27:10.387 --> 27:12.803
- How does it work
at your gym?

27:12.838 --> 27:13.908
Do people pay
to train?

27:13.942 --> 27:15.979
Or like, you know, do they--
is there a monthly fee?

27:16.013 --> 27:18.050
Or how do they--

27:18.084 --> 27:20.052
- I train them
for free.

27:20.086 --> 27:21.122
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

27:21.156 --> 27:23.365
- Just 'cause
you want to...

27:23.400 --> 27:25.264
help.

27:25.298 --> 27:26.334
- Yeah.

27:26.368 --> 27:28.163
There is--there is
nothing to charge

27:28.198 --> 27:30.200
because there is
nothing they can give.

27:30.234 --> 27:31.684
So we give
what we have.

27:31.719 --> 27:33.686
- Mm-hmm.

27:33.721 --> 27:36.862
- And--and because
they have the skills

27:36.896 --> 27:39.002
and we are there,
what do we do?

27:39.036 --> 27:41.004
We just train them.

27:41.038 --> 27:43.316
Through the training
some get employment,

27:43.351 --> 27:44.973
some become
professional fighters.

27:45.008 --> 27:47.320
They find their ways.

27:47.355 --> 27:54.327
♪

27:58.262 --> 28:01.334
[indistinct chatter]

28:07.133 --> 28:10.136
- Whatever bus you're taking,
it ain't like this.

28:10.171 --> 28:13.174
[upbeat music]

28:13.208 --> 28:16.039
Crosstown traffic just got
a little bit wilder

28:16.073 --> 28:17.350
and more fun

28:17.385 --> 28:19.076
if you're riding
the friendly skies

28:19.111 --> 28:20.837
of a matatu.

28:20.871 --> 28:24.806
♪

28:24.841 --> 28:27.809
Matatus are privately owned
and operated bus lines

28:27.844 --> 28:29.362
running regular routes,

28:29.397 --> 28:31.295
fiercely competitive
to the point

28:31.330 --> 28:35.127
that owners started making
modifications

28:35.161 --> 28:38.199
in an ever-changing range
of themes

28:38.233 --> 28:41.029
designed to attract
the fickle commuter...

28:41.064 --> 28:44.308
♪

28:44.343 --> 28:45.862
Oh, yeah.

28:45.896 --> 28:47.035
- [laughs]

28:47.070 --> 28:49.348
- [blows whistle]

28:49.382 --> 28:51.177
What up, what up, what up,
what up, what up?

28:51.212 --> 28:53.214
- It's not subtle.
All right, let's do it, man.

28:53.248 --> 28:56.493
Culminating in buses
like this,

28:56.527 --> 29:00.980
Mad Max, a rolling,
postapocalyptic,

29:01.015 --> 29:02.879
seizure-inducing
party bus.

29:02.913 --> 29:06.296
Just the thing you need
after a hard day's work.

29:06.330 --> 29:08.125
- ♪ Everyone go amok and groovy ♪

29:08.160 --> 29:09.506
- ♪ Move it, move it,
move it, move it ♪

29:09.540 --> 29:12.060
- ♪ Everyone go amok and groovy ♪

29:12.095 --> 29:14.166
- ♪ Move it, move it,
move it, move it ♪

29:14.200 --> 29:16.099
- I'm not trying
to dance!

29:16.133 --> 29:19.067
It's making me
dance!

29:19.102 --> 29:20.137
I don't actually
want to dance!

29:20.172 --> 29:21.483
- ♪ Move it

29:21.518 --> 29:23.175
- ♪ Everyone go amok and groovy ♪

29:23.209 --> 29:25.315
- So what do people want
on their matatu?

29:25.349 --> 29:26.868
What--what do they
have to have?

29:26.903 --> 29:29.112
- First of all, you
need to have good music.

29:29.146 --> 29:31.804
[upbeat dance music]

29:31.839 --> 29:34.807
The exterior arch
is to be pumping.

29:34.842 --> 29:36.050
♪

29:36.084 --> 29:38.190
- Wide-screen TVs?

29:38.224 --> 29:41.055
- Yeah, TVs, Wi-Fi,
air fresheners.

29:41.089 --> 29:43.298
- ♪ You'll be waiting
all night ♪

29:43.333 --> 29:45.162
- ♪ Everyone go amok and groovy ♪

29:45.197 --> 29:48.959
- ♪ Move it, move it,
move it, move it ♪

29:48.994 --> 29:51.479
- Oh!

29:51.513 --> 29:54.482
[upbeat music]

29:54.516 --> 29:59.901
♪

29:59.936 --> 30:02.524
- Beers and goat's head soup,
a global classic.

30:02.559 --> 30:06.183
Slow cooked, well,
goat's head.

30:06.218 --> 30:08.013
My companion,
Mr. Bell,

30:08.047 --> 30:10.981
unaccustomed as he is
to the ways of Africa,

30:11.016 --> 30:12.465
is new to
this dish.

30:12.500 --> 30:14.364
But I don't want to sound
all Colonel Mustard,

30:14.398 --> 30:16.021
but I eat this shit for
breakfast by now,

30:16.055 --> 30:17.367
you know
what I mean?

30:17.401 --> 30:20.025
- I hear the words
goat head soup

30:20.059 --> 30:22.993
and I think, oh, it'll be meat
from the goat's head in a soup.

30:23.028 --> 30:24.029
- Oh, goat head.

30:24.063 --> 30:25.616
- That--that explains why I
actually see...

30:25.651 --> 30:29.897
[laughs] a full-on
head of a goat.

30:29.931 --> 30:33.521
- Brian Wanyama Odhiambo is
a blogger, photographer,

30:33.555 --> 30:36.351
and chronicler of
the matatu phenomena.

30:36.386 --> 30:40.459
Lucia Alessandra Murotto is
a legendary conductor.

30:40.493 --> 30:43.496
Katherine Camboon is
the owner of Mad Max.

30:43.531 --> 30:46.327
[somber music]

30:46.361 --> 30:47.293
Honored guest.

30:47.328 --> 30:48.570
- Honored guest.
Is this eye--

30:48.605 --> 30:50.331
is this eye I'm eating
right here?

30:50.365 --> 30:51.677
- Soft.

30:51.711 --> 30:55.198
I generously reserve the best
and most tender bits

30:55.232 --> 30:58.097
for my friend,
as one does.

30:58.132 --> 31:05.104
♪

31:07.382 --> 31:10.075
I fear, however, that he was
less than enthusiastic,

31:10.109 --> 31:11.904
initially anyway.

31:11.939 --> 31:14.355
Wait till he tries the brain.
He's gonna love it.

31:14.389 --> 31:18.704
♪

31:18.738 --> 31:20.499
- That's
my first eye.

31:20.533 --> 31:22.535
- Yeah? All right.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

31:22.570 --> 31:25.159
I knew--I knew I'd end up doing
something like that with you.

31:25.193 --> 31:26.988
- Get it
over with then.

31:27.023 --> 31:30.026
- [laughs]
Yes.

31:30.060 --> 31:31.544
- So you own the business.
- Yeah.

31:31.579 --> 31:34.064
- And how long have you
been in the business?

31:34.099 --> 31:34.996
- Like, five years.

31:35.031 --> 31:38.206
- We want to get into
the matatu business

31:38.241 --> 31:39.725
in New York.
- Yes.

31:39.759 --> 31:41.382
[laughs]

31:41.416 --> 31:42.728
- I think it would add
some improvements.

31:42.762 --> 31:43.936
- Yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah.

31:43.971 --> 31:45.179
- We need
a hot tub.

31:45.213 --> 31:46.594
- Yeah, we need a hot--
hot tub.

31:46.628 --> 31:49.286
- What's your theme?
I already picked mine out.

31:49.321 --> 31:51.012
- See, I'm all about
counterprogramming.

31:51.047 --> 31:52.738
I would do like
the Reese Witherspoon matatu,

31:52.772 --> 31:55.154
a tribute to all of the movies
of Reese Witherspoon.

31:55.189 --> 31:56.638
[laughs]
I'm all about--

31:56.673 --> 31:58.364
I'm all about thinking
outside the box.

31:58.399 --> 32:01.195
- I'm thinking the Wolf Blitz--
"The Situation Room."

32:01.229 --> 32:02.299
- [laughs]

32:02.334 --> 32:04.681
- "The Situation Room"
matatu.

32:04.715 --> 32:07.718
This could reinvigorate public
transportation as we know it.

32:07.753 --> 32:11.067
- Especially in New York or L.A.
where people don't like the bus.

32:11.101 --> 32:15.071
[upbeat music]

32:15.105 --> 32:16.348
And what does it mean
to be conductor?

32:16.382 --> 32:19.385
They don't just let anybody
be the conductor.

32:19.420 --> 32:22.595
- In this job you need to have
a lot of patience.

32:22.630 --> 32:24.045
Just somebody who's had
a bad day,

32:24.080 --> 32:25.771
they just don't
want to pay.

32:25.805 --> 32:27.393
[blows whistle]

32:27.428 --> 32:30.086
If you don't have patience,
you just find yourself

32:30.120 --> 32:32.053
on top of the moon.

32:32.088 --> 32:33.296
[blows whistle]

32:33.330 --> 32:35.332
So when you carry people,
you need to--

32:35.367 --> 32:38.370
you need to show them that
it's--it's full of energy.

32:38.404 --> 32:42.029
- They need to know how to get
the people inside their matatu.

32:42.063 --> 32:43.754
- So the whistle
just gets everybody...

32:43.789 --> 32:45.480
- Yeah.
- Jumped up and excited.

32:45.515 --> 32:47.379
- Yeah.

32:47.413 --> 32:50.727
- Like I said, this is
a competitive business.

32:50.761 --> 32:53.074
The matatu can cost up
to 60,000 bucks

32:53.109 --> 32:54.386
to buy
and build out.

32:54.420 --> 32:57.044
Rides are only
60 cents,

32:57.078 --> 33:00.426
so to make the money back, you
better get the customers in

33:00.461 --> 33:02.566
and out
and coming back

33:02.601 --> 33:05.707
for 100,000 rides
before you break even.

33:05.742 --> 33:07.261
- [blows whistle]

33:07.295 --> 33:09.401
- So can you tell me,
what's it like

33:09.435 --> 33:14.199
growing up as
an Italian Kenyan?

33:14.233 --> 33:14.958
- Um...

33:14.993 --> 33:16.718
- I was trying
not to say white.

33:16.753 --> 33:19.204
In America, white people get
upset when you call them white.

33:19.238 --> 33:20.722
So I was
trying to--

33:20.757 --> 33:24.071
- The challenges I had
as a kid was my hair.

33:24.105 --> 33:25.348
Everyone wanted to
touch my hair.

33:25.382 --> 33:28.213
One thing I love about this job
is that

33:28.247 --> 33:31.078
I meet all types
of people,

33:31.112 --> 33:34.391
and I don't look down on them
and they don't look down on me.

33:34.426 --> 33:36.669
That's the best part
of it.

33:36.704 --> 33:41.191
[upbeat rock music]

33:41.226 --> 33:43.124
- [yelling indistinctly]

33:43.159 --> 33:44.574
- ♪ Everyone go amok and groovy ♪

33:44.608 --> 33:46.403
- ♪ Move it, move it,
move it, move it ♪

33:46.438 --> 33:48.578
- Just wait until
New York City sees

33:48.612 --> 33:51.236
Kamau and my
joint venture,

33:51.270 --> 33:53.134
the Wolf Blitzer.

